SUMMARY:Deadline: MATS Autumn 2026 Fellowship (ML Alignment and Theory Scho
 lars)
DESCRIPTION:Fully-funded AI alignment\, security and governance fellowship 
 with mentors from Anthropic\, Google DeepMind\, OpenAI\, Redwood Research 
 and other leading AI safety organisations. Fellows work on a focused resea
 rch project with mentor support during a 10-week in-person programme in Be
 rkeley (28 September - 4 December 2026). New 2026 tracks include Founding/
 Field-Building and Biosecurity in addition to the core alignment\, securit
 y and governance tracks. ELIGIBILITY: open to individual researchers\, bot
 h emerging and experienced\; no specific degree or affiliation required - 
 applications are assessed on research aptitude and track record.\n\nOrgani
 sation: MATS Research\nLocation: Berkeley\, California\, USA (in-person)\n
 Award: USD 5\,000/month stipend plus USD 8\,000/month compute budget\; hou
 sing\, meals and travel covered for the 10-week in-person phase. Approxima
 tely 80% of fellows receive a 6-12 month extension at USD 7\,680/month aft
 er the in-person phase.\nDuration: Ten weeks in-person\, 28 September - 4 
 December 2026 (with extensions for ~80% of fellows)\n\nMore: https://www.m
 atsprogram.org/apply?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
