BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:govai-dc-winter-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T105951Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: GovAI DC Winter Fellowship 2027
DESCRIPTION:GovAI's DC Winter Fellowship is a three-month bipartisan in-per
 son fellowship in Washington\, DC\, designed for individuals seeking to en
 ter or advance in US AI governance and policy. The program emphasises bipa
 rtisan engagement\, rigorous analysis\, and practical policy relevance\, w
 ith a focus on how AI policy is shaped within the US political system. Fel
 lows conduct independent research on a topic of their choice with mentorsh
 ip from a GovAI supervisor\; the first two weeks explore the AI policy lan
 dscape before a research proposal is finalised. Outputs may include a repo
 rt\, white paper\, journal article\, op-ed\, or blog post targeted at an a
 udience relevant to AI policy. Fellows also attend expert Q&As\, skills wo
 rkshops\, seminars\, work-in-progress meetings\, and social events\, and a
 re encouraged to discuss follow-on career opportunities. GovAI alumni have
  gone on to roles in US government bodies (NSC\, OSTP\, Senate\, Departmen
 t of Commerce\, DHS)\; think tanks (CSIS\, CSET\, CNAS\, RAND\, Heritage F
 oundation\, FAI)\; AI companies (OpenAI\, Anthropic\, Google DeepMind)\; a
 nd universities (Yale\, Stanford\, MIT). AMOUNT: $21\,000 stipend for thre
 e months\, plus travel support to DC and weekday lunch. Part-time fellowsh
 ip at a pro-rated salary available for DC-based think tank researchers\, g
 overnment staffers\, or professionals doing AI governance work\; pay accom
 modations possible. ELIGIBILITY: candidates must have the right to work in
  the US\; no visa sponsorship. Open to a wide range of backgrounds (govern
 ment\, academia\, industry\, civil society)\; promising undergraduates wel
 come\; no strict degree requirements. Relevant areas include public policy
 \, political science\, engineering\, computer science\, economics\, biosec
 urity\, cybersecurity\, China studies\, and risk management. SELECTION CRI
 TERIA: quality and clarity of written work\, relevant expertise\, judgemen
 t\, and team fit. APPLICATION PROCESS: (1) written application and automat
 ed abstract reasoning assessment\; (2) paid remote work test (August 2026)
 \; (3) remote interview and reference checks (September 2026)\; decisions 
 communicated October 2026. Application deadline not yet publicly stated\; 
 applications open June 2026 -- check programme page for the deadline.\n\nO
 rganisation: Centre for the Governance of AI (GovAI)\nLocation: Washington
 \, DC\, USA\; in-person\, full-time (part-time possible for DC-based think
  tank or government staff).\nAward: $21\,000 stipend for the three-month t
 erm\, plus travel support to DC and weekday lunch provided. No visa sponso
 rship. No application fee.\nDuration: 3 months\, 18 January to 9 April 202
 7.\n\nMore: https://www.governance.ai/opportunities/dc-winter-fellowship-2
 027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.governance.ai/opportunities/dc-winter-fellowship-2027?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Washington\, DC\, USA\; in-person\, full-time (part-time possible 
 for DC-based think tank or government staff).
END:VEVENT
