SUMMARY:Deadline: Horizon Institute for Public Service: AI Rapid Response F
 ellowship
DESCRIPTION:The AI Rapid Response Fellowship is a focused effort by the Hor
 izon Institute for Public Service to close the AI security talent gap in t
 he U.S. federal government. Horizon is recruiting a specialized cohort of 
 exceptional technical and policy talent to work full-time in executive bra
 nch offices on AI security-related issues\, with placements beginning as s
 oon as possible. TRACKS: the Fellow track is for candidates with technical
  or policy expertise relevant to AI security\, typically 2-6+ years of ful
 l-time relevant experience\; the Senior Fellow track is for candidates wit
 h substantial prior experience\, typically 10-15+ years in relevant techni
 cal\, policy\, or leadership roles. FOCUS: AI governance\, AI security\, p
 olicy\, and public service. COMPENSATION: Fellow track USD 170\,000-200\,0
 00+ plus a benefits stipend\; Senior Fellow track from USD 250\,000+ plus 
 a benefits stipend\, commensurate with the seniority of the placement. DUR
 ATION: one year full-time\, with the opportunity for renewal\, based in th
 e Washington\, DC area. ELIGIBILITY: U.S. citizenship is required. An exis
 ting security clearance\, or eligibility to obtain one\, is helpful but no
 t required. DEADLINE: applications are due July 22\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation
 : Horizon Institute for Public Service\nLocation: Washington\, DC area\, U
 nited States (in-person\; full-time placements in U.S. executive branch of
 fices).\nAward: Fellow track: USD 170\,000 to 200\,000+\, plus an addition
 al stipend for benefits. Senior Fellow track: from USD 250\,000+\, plus a 
 benefits stipend\, commensurate with the seniority of the placement.\nDura
 tion: One year full-time\, with the opportunity for renewal.\n\nMore: http
 s://horizonpublicservice.org/ai-rapid-response-fellowship/?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://horizonpublicservice.org/ai-rapid-response-fellowship/?utm_sour
 ce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Washington\, DC area\, United States (in-person\; full-time placem
 ents in U.S. executive branch offices).
